**************
The problem requires finding \(P(Y_7 < 27.3)\), where \(Y_7\) is the seventh order statistic of eight independent observations from a continuous distribution with the 70th percentile \(\pi_{0.7} = 27.3\). This means \(P(X_i < 27.3) = 0.7\) for each observation \(X_i\).

The event \(Y_7 < 27.3\) occurs if at least seven of the eight observations are less than 27.3. This is equivalent to the probability that a binomial random variable \(S \sim \text{Binomial}(n=8, p=0.7)\) satisfies \(S \geq 7\).

Thus,  
\[
P(S \geq 7) = P(S = 7) + P(S = 8).
\]

Calculate each term:  
\[
P(S = 7) = \binom{8}{7} (0.7)^7 (0.3)^1 = 8 \times (0.7)^7 \times 0.3,
\]  
\[
P(S = 8) = \binom{8}{8} (0.7)^8 (0.3)^0 = (0.7)^8.
\]

Compute the powers:  
\[
(0.7)^7 = 0.0823543, \quad (0.7)^8 = 0.05764801.
\]

Then,  
\[
P(S = 7) = 8 \times 0.0823543 \times 0.3 = 8 \times 0.02470629 = 0.19765032,  
\]  
\[
P(S = 8) = 0.05764801.
\]

Sum the probabilities:  
\[
P(S \geq 7) = 0.19765032 + 0.05764801 = 0.25529833.
\]

Rounding to three significant figures gives 0.255.

