(a) Find the probability that the length of life of the bulb from company $A$ exceeds the length of life of the bulb from company $B$ by at least 15 hours.
 The unit of the answer should be  .
Solution: The lengths of life for bulbs from company A and company B are normally distributed and independent. Let \(X\) be the life from company A with \(X \sim N(800, 14400)\), and \(Y\) be the life from company B with \(Y \sim N(850, 2500)\). We need \(P(X > Y + 15)\), which is equivalent to \(P(X - Y > 15)\).

