Standardize to find \(P(D > 15)\):  
\[
Z = \frac{D - \mu_D}{\sigma_D} = \frac{15 - (-50)}{130} = \frac{65}{130} = 0.5
\]  
So, \(P(D > 15) = P(Z > 0.5)\), where \(Z\) is standard normal.

From the standard normal distribution, \(P(Z \leq 0.5) \approx 0.6915\), so \(P(Z > 0.5) = 1 - 0.6915 = 0.3085\).

The probability is 0.3085, rounded to four decimal places as is reasonable for probabilities.

