\[
P(PT \text{ or } CH) = P(PT) + P(CH) - P(PT \text{ and } CH)
\]
\[
0.92 = (P(CH) + 0.16) + P(CH) - 0.28
\]
\[
0.92 = 2P(CH) - 0.12
\]
\[
0.92 + 0.12 = 2P(CH)
\]
\[
1.04 = 2P(CH)
\]
\[
P(CH) = 0.52
\]
Then:
\[
P(PT) = 0.52 + 0.16 = 0.68
\]

