From \(P(A \cup B') = 0.87\), the complement is \(P(A' \cap B) = 1 - 0.87 = 0.13\).  
The probability of \(B\) is \(P(B) = P(A \cap B) + P(A' \cap B) = P(A \cap B) + 0.13\).  
