Solution: The probability that there is at least one match when each of the 12 students rolls their 12-sided die is calculated as follows:

- The probability of no matches occurring is \((11/12)^{12}\).
- Therefore, the probability of at least one match is \(1 - (11/12)^{12}\).
- Numerically, \((11/12)^{12} \approx 0.35199588\).
- Thus, \(1 - 0.35199588 = 0.64800412\).
- Rounded to three significant figures, this is 0.648.

