Solution: The dissociation energy from the bottom of the potential well, \(D_e\), is related to the dissociation energy from the ground vibrational level, \(D_0\), by the zero-point energy (ZPE). The ZPE is calculated using the spectroscopic constants \(\omega_e = \nu_e / c = 1405.65  \text{cm}^{-1}\) and \(\omega_e x_e = \nu_e x_e / c = 23.20  \text{cm}^{-1}\).

